A '''space-filling polyhedron''' is a [[polyhedron]] that can be used to fill all of three-dimensional space via translations, rotations and/or reflections. Any periodic tiling or [[Honeycomb (geometry)|honeycomb]] of three-space can in fact be generated by translating a [[primitive cell]] polyhedron.

